<ol><li>The&nbsp;<b>line spectrum</b>&nbsp;of the star is compared with the pattern of the prominent lines in the spectrum according to the star's spectral class.</li><li>The change of wavelength of one or more prominent lines of known wavelength is measured.</li><li><b>Doppler shift</b>&nbsp;is calculated&nbsp;\(z=\frac{\Delta\lambda}{\lambda}\)<br></li><li>The speed of the star relative to Earth is calculated&nbsp;\(z=\frac{v}{c}\)</li></ol>